comment: Hood (UTA) and Thompson (GSW) briefly engage and separate away from the ball.
[Incidental or immaterial] Green (GSW) is in the paint without actively guarding an opponent for longer than three seconds.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that Hayward (UTA) was behind the three point line on his field goal was upheld.
Gobert (UTA) makes contact with Curry's (GSW) body that affects his driving shot attempt.
[Incidental or immaterial] Green (GSW) is in the paint without actively guarding an opponent for longer than three seconds.
Livingston (GSW) extends his arm as he sets the screen on Hayward (UTA) without giving him room to avoid the contact.
Green (GSW) sets the screen on Mack (UTA) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Hayward (UTA) and Curry (GSW) make incidental contact with one another while reaching for the loose ball.
[Incidental or immaterial] Green (GSW) is in the paint without actively guarding an opponent for longer than three seconds.
Curry (GSW) makes incidental contact with Mack (UTA) that does not affect his RSBQ.
Curry (GSW) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Mack (UTA) that does not affect his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Gobert (UTA) and Green (GSW) make incidental contact with one another during rebounding.
Barnes (GSW) makes contact with Mack (UTA) when he reaches in for the ball.

Livingston (GSW) falls to the floor and is immediately tied up by Mack (UTA) and Hayward (UTA) and a jump ball is correctly called. Livingston does not gain an advantage during any movement on the floor with the ball.
Green (GSW) is in the paint without actively guarding an opponent for longer than three seconds.
Livingston (GSW) extends his hip as he sets the screen on Mack (UTA) without giving him room to avoid the contact.
Green (GSW) is in the paint without actively guarding an opponent for longer than three seconds.
RHH and R-SLA show that Livingston (GSW) cleanly strips the ball from Gobert (UTA).
Hayward (UTA) makes contact with Green's (GSW) arms during his driving shot attempt.
Gobert (UTA) firms up as he sets the screen on Curry (GSW) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Hood (UTA) makes contact with Curry (GSW) that affects his RSBQ.
Livingston (GSW) sets the screen on Mack (UTA) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Mack (UTA) makes contact with Curry's (GSW) body that affects his driving shot attempt.
Curry (GSW) makes contact with Lyles (UTA) that affects his RSBQ and causes him to lose control of the ball.
Green (GSW) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Ingles's (UTA) baseline drive.
L-SLA shows that Curry (GSW) cleanly knocks the ball away from Ingles (UTA) prior to any incidental arm contact.
Ingles (UTA) establishes and maintains a legal guarding position during Curry's (GSW) driving layup attempt.
[Incidental or immaterial] Green (GSW) is in the paint without actively guarding an opponent for longer than three seconds.
Curry (GSW) establishes a legal guarding position and Hayward (UTA) dislodges him by dropping his shoulder into him and then extends his arm after the contact.
Green (GSW) legally contests Hayward (UTA) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Thompson (GSW) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Mack's (UTA) drive and pass attempt.
Lyles (UTA) commits a take foul on Green (GSW).
Lyles (UTA) makes incidental contact with Green (GSW) during rebounding.
RATR shows that Thompson (GSW) makes contact with the ball as he defends Lyles's (UTA) shot attempt.
